news.title: Evergrande to sell project in eastern China for $200 million
news.para: Saddled with more than $300 billion in liabilities, Evergrande has been struggling to repay suppliers, creditors and complete projects.

news.title: China's Greenland Holdings seeks to extend $488 million bond payment
news.para: Shanghai-based Greenland is the first state-backed developer to extend a dollar bond payment since the country's property sector plunged into a debt crisis last year.

news.title: WeWork appoints Andre Fernandez as CFO
news.para: Fernandez, who most recently served as the CFO and executive vice president of enterprise technology provider NCR Corp , will assume office on June 10, the company said.

news.title: Chinese city Zhaoqing eases rules to support property developers' cashflow
news.para: Analysts said the third-tier city in Guangdong province with a population of 4.1 million is the first in China to introduce guidelines specifically to help developers' liquidity, a move they said other cities may follow.

news.title: India Cements posts net loss of Rs 10.58 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Its revenue from operations was down 3.72 per cent to Rs 1,417.62 crore during the quarter under review, as against Rs 1,472.45 crore in the corresponding period a year ago.

news.title: Akzo Nobel India's profit at Rs 75 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Revenue from operations was higher at Rs 867.1 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 781.4 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Jindal group to set up cement plant in Raigarh
news.para: Principal secretary (commerce and industry) Manoj Kumar Pingua and Jindal corporate affairs president Pradeep Tandon signed the MOU for setting up the plant, which will have a target to produce 25 lakh tonnes of cement and 25 lakh tonnes of clinker per year.

news.title: Chandigarh: Now, file property tax with rebate till July 31
news.para: Chandigarh administration, on Thursday, extended the date of filing property tax for two months with rebate facility. However, no decision has been taken about exemption on the tax amount. The tax has been imposed on colonies in the city for the first time.

news.title: Aurum PropTech buys HelloWorld Technologies India and CareerSocially
news.para: The two 100% buyouts have taken the company’s acquisition tally to six totalling over Rs 233 crores investment made by the company over the last one year after being acquired by Aurum Ventures in June 2021.

news.title: Govt to look into pleas to tweak RERA for redevelopment: Maharashtra housing minister
news.para: The state government has brought down the consent of members from 70% to 51% for the redevelopment of housing societies.

news.title: Berger Paints' net profit up 5.6% to Rs 220 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Revenue from operations was up 7.96 per cent at Rs 2,187.51 crore during the quarter as against Rs 2,026.09 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Rs 747 crore to speed up Kanpur Metro project
news.para: This fund allocation would speed up the Kanpur Metro work. At present, the Metro runs between IIT and Motijheel on a nine-kilometre elevated track.

news.title: Geo-mapping of houses in municipal areas on cards: Goa minister
news.para: Rane said that this exercise would be only so that civic bodies have live records available to them. People need not to worry because it would not increase any tax.

news.title: Four illegal colonies in Greater Noida demolished
news.para: The action was carried out by the Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) on instructions of its CEO Surendra Singh, the officials said.

news.title: Dozens of landmark buildings under redevelopment in Ahmedabad
news.para: While Ahmedabad is expanding across its length and breadth with new projects being launched in most areas, areas such as Navrangpura, Vastrapur, Paldi, Vasna and Shahibaug – which are replete with key residential and commercial buildings – are increasingly witnessing redevelopment schemes and buyouts.
